task.summary: - Bug fixes - Add a button for 2.14.4 "Only extract from the current giveaway onward" (close #946) - Add option to reset left/right main page heading buttons order (close #958) - Extend new draggable system to left/right main page heading buttons (close #957) - Fix a bug that does not show giveaway info category for games with 0P (close #949)
- Bug fix for #946 - Only build ESGST.user.js during production
- Bug fixes - Add option to use different pause settings in Endless Scrolling depending on the include path (close #959)

- Add option to display time to point cap alongside with points at the header (close #961) - Add option to automatically bookmark giveaways when trying to enter them without enough points to Enter/Leave Giveaway Button (close #962) - Extract ItsTooHard and Jigidi links with Giveaway Extractor (close #963) - Add option to categorize Steam games to Multi Manager (close #964) - Bug fixes
- Bug fixes - Add new section to the settings menu to handle elements order and prevent them from being draggable in all pages (close #960)
- Bug fixes - Add which games were won from the listed users to User Giveaway Data (close #956) - Add "Winners" giveaway filter (close #965)
- Fix a bug that refreshes the page after commenting with Multi-Reply (close #969) - Fix a bug that does not show replies in the inbox page with Reply From Inbox (close #970)
- Add a new feature: Visible Full Level (close #966)
- Make Level Progress Visualizer and Points Visualizer compatible (close #967)
- Add option to change Level Progress Visualizer and Points Visualizer bar colors (close #968)
- Fix a style issue that lowers the opacity of the points/copies elements (close #973)
- Make Level Progress Visualizer and Points Visualizer bars dynamically adjust to the size of the button (close #974)

- Fix a style issue with game categories that are moved to the giveaway columns (close #979) - Fix a bug that duplicates game categories (close #980) - Fix a bug in Giveaway Winners Link (close #981) - Fix a style issue in Grid View (close #982)
- Add option to use preferred Google/Microsoft account when restoring/backing up (close #978)
- Load package data without having to reload the page in Game Categories (close #922)
